M4: Slint UI - conflicts list, side-by-side diff, apply with preview, undo

Closes milestone:m4. dcsbinder-ui.exe is a single-window app that
auto-discovers DCS installs, scans + enumerates live controllers on a
background thread, and lets the user resolve every conflict or orphan
through a side-by-side diff view + mandatory plan-preview before apply.

UI surfaces (ui/main.slint):
- Top status bar: scan summary, DCS-running indicator (red banner
  disables apply), Rescan and Undo-last buttons.
- Installs panel: every discovered DCS root (DCS, openbeta, serverbeta)
  with aircraft + active-file counts.
- Left list: actionable items, color-coded:
  CONFLICT rows = two-GUID groups (the M1 detection).
  ORPHAN rows = single stale GUID with a live device of the same name
    whose GUID is not represented by any file. (The LftPnl case.)
  Each candidate is annotated LIVE (green) or STALE.
- Right pane: side-by-side diff (line-level via the similar crate),
  with header buttons Use A / Use B for conflicts and Remap-to-live
  for orphans.
- Plan dialog (modal overlay): shows the FULL plan - backup dir,
  from/to GUIDs, aircraft+mutation counts, every mutation line.
  Confirm/Cancel buttons. Apply runs core::remap::execute on a thread
  and reports the .done path or error back via invoke_from_event_loop.

Core (M3 reuse):
- conflict::detect_orphans new function: finds single-candidate groups
  whose GUID does not match a live device with the same product name.
  Lets the UI surface bindings that need to be re-keyed to the live
  GUID even when there is no two-GUID conflict.

Rust glue (src/main.rs):
- AppData state guarded by a Mutex; scan runs on std::thread::spawn,
  results pushed via slint::invoke_from_event_loop.
- Diff rendered as a Vec<DiffSegment{text,kind}>; the slint view colors
  insert/delete/context.
- Plan preview reuses core::remap::plan; execute is gated behind the
  Confirm button. DCS-running check enabled (engine refuses if true).
- Undo-last walks %APPDATA%/DCSBinder/backups/ for the most-recent
  .done manifest and calls core::remap::undo.

Stack:
- slint = 1.13 pinned (CLAUDE.md rule).
- backend-winit + renderer-skia for crisp rendering.
- similar = 2 for line-level text diff.

Tests: 24 workspace tests still green (no UI tests yet - the UI is
thin glue over the core).

Smoke-tested by building dcsbinder-ui.exe (~27 MB release). Visual
verification deferred to user; the binary is at:
target/release/dcsbinder-ui.exe

CI gate green: fmt, clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings,
test --workspace.

